If you’re a parent, you understand the constant struggle of finding fun, interesting and cheap things to do with your kid/kids on the weekends in LA. Phoenix and I found this cool spot @offroadclubsimivalley, you can drive their remote controlled trucks on a off road track. Phoenix had a blast and really enjoyed himself, and one hidden benefit is that right next door is a Colombian food truck, they had the most authentic and amazing food. Phoenix and I will definitely be back to visit again 😊💪🏽🙌🏽

My heart is heavy with grief at my brother David’s passing. He was a good man, after suffering a horrific injury supporting our troops in Afghanistan, he never let his  injury slow him down or diminish his lust for life. I I had an immense.amount of pride in him for the way he fought back and refused to voice regret or feel sorry for himself.
He just lived his life fully, with no excuses and no regrets.
❤️❤️❤️

.

Phoenix and I spent yesterday in Long Beach at the Jonathan Jacques Cancer Institute charity event called The Champions Run For Life, this event benefits their pediatric cancer patients. I plan my year around making sure I’m available whenever this event happens. Despite manny of these children being really I’ll, it’s easy to forget that for a little while because they are amazing to be around. They are  courageous, brave and resilient. My mom taught me that volunteering is how we give back to our community and now Im making sure to teach this to my son.
.

What a day yesterday was, Phoenix’s movie @freelunch.movie premiered at the Chinese theater in Hollywood to a sold out crowd. Phoenix did the red carpet with the rest of the cast and director. Later in the evening at the film festival award show, the film  won Best Youth Ensemble, was voted the audience award winner and won Best feature film by a female director. I feel so blessed that I’ve been able to witness all of and cheer my son on. I am so very proud of this kid and the entire cast, the movie was so good!

It feels like just yesterday I was the dad of an adorable little boy who made my heart melt every other second. I blinked my eyes and that little boy turns 13 today. Now he’s only 2-3 inches shorter than me, and his damn feet are the same size as mine.
I’m so proud of the young man Phoenix has become, A multi award winning actor, an honor roll student in middle school, a gentle soul with a kind heart. I am immensely fortunate to have been blessed with this kid.
But I do wish I could turn back the clock to keep him my little boy just a bit longer😔😔
.
.
.
.
.

This breaks my heart in two. The oldest daughter was a friend of Phoenix’s from his current middle school. I knew Christian, hung out with him at his house. A really good guy, with a great personality, a talented actor, and a loving single dad for his two young daughters. Phoenix and I are both heartbroken and trying to fully process the death of all three of them. My sincere condolences to his entire family. 🙏🏼🙏🏼🙏🏼🙏🏼😞😞😞😞
